      <akn:section eId="sec_18_109">
        <akn:num>18-109</akn:num>
        <akn:heading>Revocation of wills; revival.</akn:heading>
<akn:subsection eId="subsec_18-109_a">
      <akn:num>(a)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A will or codicil, or a part thereof, may not be revoked, except by implication of law, otherwise than by</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection><akn:subsection eId="subsec_18-109_b">
      <akn:num>(b)</akn:num>
      <akn:content><akn:p>A will or codicil, or a part thereof, after it is revoked, may not be revived otherwise than by its re-execution, or by a codicil executed as provided in the case of wills, and then only to the extent to which an intention to revive is shown.</akn:p></akn:content>
    </akn:subsection>
      </akn:section>
